A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
To express support for the continued operations of the Louisiana National Guard at Camp
Beauregard and to commend the accomplishments of the Louisiana National Guard
Youth Challenge Program.
WHEREAS, Camp Beauregard is located in Pineville, Louisiana, and has a long
history of supporting the training and mobilization of the United States military that dates
back to World War I and continues through present-day; the installation serves as the
primary annual training and pre-mobilization training platform for the Louisiana National
Guard; and
WHEREAS, the mission of Camp Beauregard is to support federal and state military
and emergency operations; and
WHEREAS, Camp Beauregard provides quality training and training support
resources and facilities for pre-mobilization and post-mobilization; the camp also serves as
both a staging base and logistical staging area for various emergency response agencies
during times of state and federal emergencies; and
WHEREAS, Camp Beauregard hosts one of the three Louisiana National Guard
Youth Challenge Programs, which works to instill values, life skills, education, and self-
discipline in Louisiana's youth; the program is an alternative educational program that offers
youth, from ages sixteen to eighteen, the opportunity to change their future, and it is geared
towards students seeking a way to succeed outside of a traditional school setting while
working to obtain a high school equivalency diploma; and
