WHEREAS, the Louisiana National Guard Youth Challenge Program encourages
teamwork, personal growth, and development through eight core components: life coping
skills, academic excellence, job skills, responsible citizenship, leadership/followership,
health and hygiene, service to the community, and physical fitness; and
WHEREAS, the Youth Challenge Program is a seventeen-month program consisting
of two phases: a five-month residential phase and a twelve-month post-residential phase;
during the residential phase, students live on-site at one of three locations: Camp Minden
near Shreveport, Camp Beauregard Training Center, and The Gillis W. Long Center near
Baton Rouge; during phase one, students attend school and receive counseling and twenty-
four-hour supervision; and
WHEREAS, after graduation, students return home to begin a twelve-month post-
residential phase; this phase is designed to help students continue in a positive direction, and
graduates are assisted by Youth Challenge Program case managers and community mentors
to continue their education, enroll in college, begin job training, find employment, or enlist
in the military; and
WHEREAS, the Louisiana National Guard at Camp Beauregard is most deserving
of the highest recognition for its longstanding efforts to support the United States military
and Louisiana's youth.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
express support for the continued operations of the Louisiana National Guard at Camp
Beauregard in Pineville, Louisiana, and does hereby commend the accomplishments of the
Louisiana National Guard Youth Challenge.
